          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Neutron capture cross sections of 148Gd and the",
                " decay of 149Gd"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "REAC"
                ],
                "institute": "1USAORU"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The irradiations were performed in the",
                "  TRIGA reactor at Oregon State University."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "REAC"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Three different irradiation facilities were",
                " used: an in-core irradiation tube (ICIT); a",
                " cadmium-lined in-core irradiation tube (CLICIT), with",
                " a negligible thermal flux (below a cutoff of 0.5 eV)",
                " and the same epithermal flux as the ICIT; and a",
                " thermal column (TC)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The gamma rays were counted using a high purity",
                " Ge (HPGe) detector connected to a digital spectroscopy",
                " system. The detector had an active volume of 169 cm3",
                " and a resolution of 1.65 keV for the 1.33-MeV gamma",
                " ray of 60Co (with an efficiency of 35% compared with",
                " NaI)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Radioactive source material of 148Gd (a pure a emitter",
                " with a half-life of 75 yr) was obtained from two",
                " suppliers: Los Alamos National Laboratory and Isotope",
                " Products Laboratory. Both samples were in the form of",
                " a dilute HCl solution. For the cross section",
                " measurements, small quantities of the liquid were",
                " sealed in either polyethylene vials or quartz ampoules",
                " for irradiation. In some cases the liquid was",
                " evaporated to dryness prior to irradiation and then",
                " taken up with fresh HCl after irradiation.",
                "In addition to the 149Gd, immediately after the",
                " irradiation our samples contained about 0.7% 152Eu,",
                " 0.1% 154Eu, 2% 151Gd, and 0.5% 153Gd.",
                "The samples also contained small amounts of short-lived",
                " 82Br (produced from neutron activation of Br which is",
                " a contamination in HCl)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " For the spectroscopic studies of the 149Gd",
                " decay, three different samples were prepared by",
                " irradiating quantities of 148Gd activity each",
                " approximately 103 times stronger than was used for the",
                " cross section determinations."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "For the determination of the neutron fluxes, we used a",
                " variety of flux monitors: 59Co and 197Au in dilute Al",
                " alloys served as primary flux monitors, and 58Fe,",
                " 64Zn, and 94,96Zr were used as secondary flux",
                " monitors. All flux monitors were in the form of thin",
                " metal foils of natural isotopic abundances and were",
                " irradiated simultaneously with the 148Gd."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "HISTORY": [
            {
